	                                <p>Hey Andrew!</p><p>You've already got the right fix actually! This tutorial was on Symfony 2, where we did things like "new MovieType" and -&gt;add('someField', 'text'). In Symfony 3, change it to MovieType::class (you already did this) *and* make a similar change in your form class - e.g. -&gt;add('someField', TextType::class); That'll fix things :).</p><p>Cheers!</p>
